dct_description_sm: Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator grid added, 1948. Copied 1948 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Indianapolis East, 1948. Original map compiled by USGS from planetable surveys and stereophotogrammetric methods, 1946. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS.  Sheet issued as 7.5 minute quadrangle.  At head of map: Sheet 3763 I SE, A.M.S. series V851.   Includes Index to boundaries and Index to adjoining sheets.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1949.
Dimensions: 56 x 43 cm, on sheet 74 x 56 cm; Scale: 1:25,000
